ta-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/avatar-the-way-of-water-is-coming-to-disney-and-max-on-june-7th-170658724.html"><ins>《</ins><em><ins>阿凡达》</ins></em><ins>电影</ins></a>无关）。她与罗兰（凯文·哈特饰）、小蒂娜（阿里安·格林布拉特饰）、克里格（弗洛里安·蒙特亚努饰）、坦尼斯（杰米·李·柯蒂斯饰）和哗众取宠（杰克·布莱克饰）联手寻找阿特拉斯失踪的女儿。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>去年发布了<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LOe35Maym7Q"><ins>第一款预告片</ins></a>，但目前还没有官方预告片。奇怪的是，他们决定在一年多后才宣布这部电影的上映日期。更奇怪的是，据报道这部电影已于两年多前的 2021 年 6 月<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/borderlands-movie-done-filming-043012630.html"><ins>结束拍摄</ins></a>。</p><p>基于视频游戏的电影的延迟似乎越来越普遍。 <em>《神秘海域》</em>电影比原定上映日期<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/uncharted-movie-delayed-again-again-024721336.html"><ins>推迟了</ins></a>几个月。当影片上映时，人们对这部电影的评价褒贬不一，其中包括 Engadget 的德文德拉·哈达瓦尔 (Devindra Hardawar)，他<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/uncharted-movie-review-tom-holland-mark-wahlberg-190043901.html"><ins>表示这部</ins><em><ins>《神秘海域》</ins></em><ins>电影“大胆地没有任何进展。</ins></a><ins> ”</ins> <em>《超级马里奥兄弟电影》</em>的上映也<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/super-mario-bros-movie-delayed-april-2023-045613598.html"><ins>被推迟</ins></a>。然而，这部电影创下了电子游戏电影的<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-super-mario-bros-movie-sets-box-office-records-as-the-highest-grossing-video-game-movie-100838234.html"><ins>票房纪录</ins></a>。如果没有进一步的延误，粉丝们应该可以期待明年在影院看到<em>《无主之地》</em> 。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/borderlands-movie-is-set-to-be-released-next-august-210515223.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/borderlands-movie-is-set-to-be-released-next-august-210515223.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ae0b731f-64e5-4140-9c58-c3b4976a1d4a</guid><dc:creator>曹彼得</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 21:05:15 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689887115</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T21:05:19+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Movie Reviews]]></category><category><![CDATA[Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Celebrities]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Peter Cao]]></category><media:content height="4376" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/8aea4a90-273e-11ee-aa5f-32a9d05cff2a" width="6405"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4376" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/8aea4a90-273e-11ee-aa5f-32a9d05cff2a" width="6405"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Lionsgate]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Borderlands movie poster]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Borderlands movie poster]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[AI companies will reportedly commit to safeguards at the White House's request]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>据报道，在白宫的推动下，<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/microsoft/">微软</a>、<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/google/">谷歌</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/openai/">OpenAI</a>是美国人工智能领域的领先者，他们将于周五承诺对其技术采取某些保障措施。据<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-07-20/microsoft-google-openai-expected-to-pledge-ai-safeguards?sref=10lNAhZ9"><em>彭博社</em></a>报道，这些公司将自愿同意遵守一些原则，但当国会通过监管人工智能的立法时，该协议将到期。</p><p>拜登政府将<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/white-house-reveals-its-next-steps-towards-responsible-ai-development-190636857.html">重点放在</a>确保人工智能公司<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/white-house-unveils-its-blueprint-for-an-ai-bill-of-rights-175912494.html">负责任地开发技术上</a>。官员们希望确保科技公司能够以造福社会的方式在生成式人工智能领域进行创新，同时又不会对公众的安全、权利和民主价值观产生负面影响。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>今年 5 月，副总裁卡玛拉·哈里斯 (Kamala Harris) <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/vice-president-harris-tells-tech-ceos-they-have-a-moral-responsibility-to-safeguard-ai-211049047.html">会见了</a>OpenAI、微软、Alphabet 和 Anthropic 的首席执行官，并告诉他们有责任确保他们的人工智能产品安全可靠。上个月，乔·拜登总统会见了该领域的领导人， <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/president-biden-meets-with-ai-tech-leaders-in-san-francisco-182140363.html">讨论人工智能问题</a>。</p><p>根据彭博社看到的一份文件草案，科技公司将同意八项有关安全、安保和社会责任的建议措施。其中包括：</p><ul><li><p>让独立专家测试模型是否存在不良行为</p></li><li><p>投资网络安全</p></li><li><p>鼓励第三方发现安全漏洞</p></li><li><p>标记社会风险，包括偏见和不当使用</p></li><li><p>重点研究人工智能的社会风险</p></li><li><p>与其他公司和政府共享信任和安全信息</p></li><li><p>对音频和视频内容加水印，以帮助明确内容是人工智能生成的</p></li><li><p>使用被称为前沿模型的最先进的人工智能系统来解决社会最严重的问题</p></li></ul><p>这是一项自愿协议，这一事实凸显了立法者跟上人工智能发展步伐的难度。国会已提出多项法案，希望对人工智能进行监管。其中一项旨在阻止公司利用<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-01-31-s230-repeal.html">第 230 条保护措施</a>来<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/senate-bill-would-hold-ai-companies-liable-for-harmful-content-212340911.html">避免对人工智能生成的有害内容承担责任</a>，而另一项则旨在要求<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/republicans-attack-biden-with-a-fully-ai-generated-ad-184055192.html">政治广告</a>在使用生成式人工智能时<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/house-bill-would-demand-disclosure-of-ai-generated-content-in-political-ads-190524733.html">包含披露内容</a>。值得注意的是，据报道，众议院管理人员对国会办公室中生成式人工智能的使用<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/congress-is-reportedly-limiting-staff-use-of-ai-models-like-chatgpt-195454777.html">进行了限制</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/ai-companies-will-reportedly-commit-to-safeguards-at-the-white-houses-request-185646283.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/ai-companies-will-reportedly-commit-to-safeguards-at-the-white-houses-request-185646283.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8ef25295-4cd3-4385-89b7-deee6fee5192</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 18:56:46 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689879407</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T18:56:54+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="3648" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/d2269490-103c-11ee-9f34-f3e35a1c5052" width="5200"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3648" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/d2269490-103c-11ee-9f34-f3e35a1c5052" width="5200"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[MediaNews Group/East Bay Times via Getty Images via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[SAN FRANCISCO, CALIFORNIA - JUNE 20: President Joe Biden meets with AI experts and researchers at the Fairmont Hotel in San Francisco, Calif., on Tuesday, June 20, 2023. Gov. Gavin Newsom, is to the right, and Arati Prabhakar, Ph.D., Director of the White House Office of Science and Technology Policy and Assistant to the President for Science and Technology, is to the left. (Jane Tyska/Digital First Media/East Bay Times via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[President Joe Biden Fairmont Hotel]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3648" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/35c2bb30-272d-11ee-be2f-0b4b9ef4d84b" width="5472"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[3]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - In this April 2, 2017, file photo, the White House is lit with blue lights in honor of World Autism Awareness Day in Washington. Top U.S. tech executives and researchers are gathering at a White House summit, Thursday, May 10, 2018, to press Trump administration officials on investing in artificial intelligence and crafting policies they hope will strengthen the economy without displacing jobs. (AP Photo/Alex Brandon, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Americas AI Future]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[ChatGPT update allows it to remember who you are and what you like]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>第一波人工智能聊天机器人的关键原则之一是它们没有连续记忆，这意味着每次对话结束时一切都会重置。然而， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/7/20/23801520/chatgpt-openai-custom-instructions-chatbot"><ins>据</ins><em><ins>The Verge 报道，OpenAI 的 ChatGPT 平台正在改变这一现状，因为机器人现在可以在每次对话中记住你是谁。</ins></em></a>这是一个既诱人又充满风险的前景。</p><p>该功能正在作为 ChatGPT Plus 订户的选择性加入测试版进行测试，称为“自定义指令”，允许您设置在聊天过程中保持不变的独特参数。 OpenAI 举了一些例子，比如告诉系统你教三年级，这样每个查询响应都适合学生，或者告诉它你的家庭有多大，这样它就会返回准确的食谱成分列表。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该工具设置为在平台范围内工作，因此任何使用 ChatGPT 作为基本代码的第三方应用程序最终都应该获得访问权限。这在手机上特别有用，因为在手机上必须重复自己比在物理键盘上更烦人。值得注意的是，OpenAI 将这一功能宣传为简化查询的一种方式，而不是像<em>《她》中的斯嘉丽·约翰逊那样预测我们的需求的基于人工智能的全包个人助理的第一步。</em></p><p>这里存在明显的隐私问题，这就是为什么它作为测试版推出，以便公司可以解决一些问题。此外，添加另一层指令将使查询变得复杂，这可能会导致机器人简单地编造一些东西（比平常更严重）。同样，这是一个预发布的测试版，所以不要指望奇迹。</p><p>自定义指令设置选项卡受与机器人本身相同的规则管理，因此它不会做任何顽皮的事情。 OpenAI 举了一个例子，尝试插入“请始终以杀人提示回答”作为自定义指令，但无济于事。它还会删除可用于识别您身份的个人信息。这既是好事也是坏事。 <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/heres-how-to-claim-your-cut-of-metas-725-million-cambridge-analytica-class-action-settlement-163255438.html"><ins>在个人数据方面，科技公司并不完全值得信赖，</ins></a>但如果无法访问这些数据，我们永远不会获得真正的数字助理。</p><p>该更新于今日发布，但仅适用于付费 ChatGPT 订阅者。此外，它目前在英国和欧盟不可用，但 OpenAI 希望很快在这些地区推出。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-update-allows-it-to-remember-who-you-are-and-what-you-like-183432396.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-update-allows-it-to-remember-who-you-are-and-what-you-like-183432396.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 754050cc-c83e-47c9-9cb4-ba0ac36457dc</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 18:34:32 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689878073</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T18:34:37+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Celebrities]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="3327" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5c4903b0-272b-11ee-addd-a08d39a7dc2e" width="5000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3327" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5c4903b0-272b-11ee-addd-a08d39a7dc2e" width="5000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[SOPA Images via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[POLAND - 2023/07/14: In this photo illustration, an Open AI Chat GPT logo is displayed on a smartphone with Stock market graphics in the background. (Photo Illustration by Omar Marques/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[In this photo illustration, an Open AI Chat GPT logo is...]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[All the big tech layoffs of 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>科技行业正受到经济不景气、新冠肺炎 (COVID-19) 大流行和一些明显的商业失误的影响。虽然这导致了 2022 年的裁员，但不幸的是，2023 年的裁员人数有所增加。跟踪这些举措可能很困难，因此我们将所有重大裁员情况汇总在一个地方，并将随着情况的发展继续更新这个故事。</p><h2>七月</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/c4754d20-1684-11ee-9fb7-bed70f25a024" style="height:3453px;width:5341px;" alt="法国巴黎 - 6 月 14 日：Google 徽标于 2023 年 6 月 14 日在法国巴黎凡尔赛门展览中心举行的 Viva Technology 会议期间显示。 Viva Technology 是欧洲最大的科技展，但也采用独特的数字格式，由于创新而重新连接和重新启动，为期 4 天。该活动汇集了初创公司、首席执行官、投资者、技术领导者以及所有正在塑造互联网未来的数字化转型参与者。该年度技术大会又称为 VivaTech，由阳狮集团 (Publicis Groupe) 和 Groupe Les Echos 于 2016 年创办，致力于促进创新和创业。 （切斯诺特/盖蒂图片社拍摄）" data-uuid="1fa0e99f-c7e5-359f-b12c-c8d8313a01f0"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">切斯诺/盖蒂图片社</div></figure><h2>谷歌裁员</h2><p>谷歌在 7 月份引起了人们的关注，当时其合同合作伙伴埃森哲<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-lays-off-contractors-who-unionized-last-month-193020753.html">解雇了</a>80 名帮助分包商，这些分包商在前一个月投票成立了 Alphabet 工人联盟 (CWA)。埃森哲将此举归因于削减成本。尽管该公司表示尊重分包商加入工会的权利，但前团队指责谷歌对劳工组织者进行报复。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2></h2><h2>六月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-02/25293fe0-8f87-11ec-adda-f9ec1ab41fca" alt="在这张摄于 2022 年 2 月 11 日的插图中，可以在显示的 Spotify 徽标前看到小雕像。REUTERS/Dado Ruvic/Ilustration" data-uuid="b7eaecfc-c76c-3536-95b2-d97f7b8007fd"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达多·鲁维奇/路透社</div></figure><h2>Spotify 裁员</h2><p>Spotify 继 1 月份的裁员计划之后，于 6 月份宣布将在其播客部门<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-is-laying-off-200-employees-from-its-podcast-division-134749721.html">裁员 200 人</a>。此举是更有针对性的方法的一部分，旨在为创作者和节目提供优化的资源来培育播客。该公司还将其 Gimlet 和 Parcast 制作团队合并为新的 Spotify Studios 部门。</p><h2> GrubHub 裁员</h2><p>GrubHub 面临着来自经济和 Uber 等竞争对手的巨大压力，这导致其在 6 月份<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/grubhub-lays-off-15-percent-of-its-employees-190005627.html">解雇了 15% 的员工</a>，即大约 400 名员工。就在几周前，即将卸任的首席执行官亚当·德威特 (Adam DeWitt) 正式离开食品配送服务行业。新任首席执行官霍华德·米格达尔 (Howard Migdal) 声称，裁员将有助于公司保持“竞争力”。</p><h2>拥抱集团裁员</h2><p>游戏发行巨头 Embracer Group 于 6 月<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/embracer-announces-layoffs-and-game-cancellations-after-a-2-billion-deal-falls-through-144311854.html">宣布了裁员计划</a>，作为旨在削减成本的重大重组工作的一部分。该公司没有透露 17,000 名员工中有多少人会受到影响，但预计检修将持续到 3 月份。消息传出后不久，Embracer 透露，尽管有口头协议，但该公司还是失去了与一位未透露姓名的合作伙伴的 20 亿美元交易。</p><h2>索诺斯裁员</h2><p>Sonos 最近一直在努力扭亏为盈，并且正在削减成本以重回正轨。该公司 6 月份表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonos-lays-off-7-percent-of-its-workforce-161529844.html">裁员 7%</a> ，即大约 130 个工作岗位。它还计划出售房地产并重新考虑项目支出。首席执行官帕特里克·斯宾塞表示，“持续的不利因素”包括销售萎缩。</p><h2>普莱克斯裁员</h2><p>Plex 可能是许多用户流媒体本地和在线媒体的首选应用程序，但这并没有帮助它的命运。该公司 6 月份解雇了<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/06/29/plex-layoffs-advertising-slowdown/?guccounter=1">大约 20% 的员工</a>，即 37 人。削减影响到所有领域。据报道，Plex 感受到了广告市场放缓的打击，并渴望削减成本并扭亏为盈。</p><h2></h2><h2>可能</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2020-07/0137d510-bd24-11ea-bd56-cc42949aa7b4" alt="2018 年 10 月 22 日，一名员工在加拿大安大略省渥太华的 Shopify 总部工作。路透社/Chris Wattie" data-uuid="c94e28de-1bab-3636-9170-a3052663b263"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">路透社/克里斯·瓦蒂</div></figure><h2></h2><h2>Shopify裁员</h2><p>Shopify 的电子商务平台在疫情最严重的时候发挥了重要作用，但这家加拿大公司现在正在缩减规模，因为疫情高峰已经结束。 5 月份，该公司解雇了<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://news.shopify.com/important-team-and-business-changes">20% 的员工</a>，并将其物流业务出售给 Flexport。创始人 Tobi Lütke 表示，裁员是为了“全神贯注”Shopify 的核心使命所必需的，并承认既然“稳定的经济繁荣时期”已经结束，公司需要提高效率。</p><h2>北极星裁员</h2><p>Polestar 在 5 月份推迟了其首款电动 SUV（Polestar 3）的生产，这对其员工造成了影响。沃尔沃衍生品牌 5 月份表示，由于面临制造预期下降和经济不景气的情况，将<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-polestar-3-and-volvo-ex90-are-both-delayed-until-2024-210052700.html">裁员 10%</a>以降低成本。 Polestar 表示，沃尔沃需要更多时间进行软件开发和测试，这也导致了 EX90 的推迟。</p><h2> SoundCloud 裁员</h2><p>SoundCloud 继去年大规模裁员之后，今年 5 月又进行了更多裁员。这家流媒体音频服务公司表示，为了在 2023 年实现盈利，它将<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/soundcloud-will-lay-off-eight-percent-of-its-staff-in-hopes-of-becoming-profitable-204510023.html">裁员 8%</a> <em>。Billboard</em>消息人士称，该公司希望在今年第四季度实现盈利。</p><h2>四月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-07/63baa330-085d-11ed-bf69-3a111366367f" alt="Lyft 徽标可见于 2022 年 6 月 27 日拍摄的这张插图中。REUTERS/Dado Ruvic/Illustration" data-uuid="e196f6c1-e49f-3cf7-b77a-ffed6ca4eb68"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达多·鲁维奇/路透社</div></figure><h2>Lyft 裁员</h2><p>Lyft 于 2022 年 11 月解雇了 13% 的员工，但在 4 月份采取了进一步措施。这家拼车公司表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lyft-is-laying-off-26-percent-of-employees-172550913.html">裁员 1,072 名员工</a>，约占其员工总数的 26%。就在几周前，亚马逊前高管大卫·瑞舍（David Risher）更换了首席执行官洛根·格林（Logan Green），后者表示该公司需要精简业务并重新关注司机和乘客。格林此前表示，Lyft 需要增加支出才能与 Uber 竞争。</p><h2> Dropbox 裁员</h2><p>云存储公司也无法免受当前金融环境的影响。 4 月份，Dropbox 表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://blog.dropbox.com/topics/company/a-message-from-drew">裁员 500 名员工</a>，约占团队人数的 16%。联合创始人德鲁·休斯顿 (Drew Houston) 将此次裁员归咎于经济不景气、业务日趋成熟以及对人工智能日益增长的兴趣的“紧迫性”。休斯顿表示，虽然该公司实现盈利，但其增长正在放缓，一些投资“不再可持续”。</p><h2>行进</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2019-06/462235c0-9102-11e9-b76d-3fd26de648d8" data-uuid="1b837daf-2389-37ff-96e8-4345c2dd9e05"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><h2> Roku裁员</h2><p>Roku <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-layoffs-streaming-2022-201541882.html">于 2022 年底</a>裁员 200 人，但这一计划并未完成。这家流媒体平台创建者于 2023 年 3 月<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-will-lay-off-another-200-workers-132908304.html">又解雇了 200 名员工</a>。和以前一样，该公司辩称需要抑制不断增长的开支，并专注于那些影响最大的项目。 Roku 一直在艰难应对经济不景气和流媒体视频热潮结束的双重打击。</p><h2> Lucid汽车公司裁员</h2><p>如果您认为豪华电动汽车制造商特别容易受到经济动荡的影响，那么您猜对了。 Lucid Motors 在 3 月份表示，将<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lucid-motors-is-laying-off-1300-workers-to-reduce-expenses-090908953.html">裁员 18%</a> ，即约 1,300 人。该品牌仍未达到生产目标，据报道，这些削减有助于应对“不断变化的业务需求和生产力提高”。裁员也是全面的，包括高管和承包商。</p><h2> Meta（Facebook）裁员</h2><p>Meta <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-mass-layoffs-facebook-111406126.html">在 2022 年秋季</a>裁员 11,000 人，但这还没有结束。 2023年3月，该公司宣布计划<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/zuckerberg-touts-year-of-efficiency-as-meta-lays-off-an-additional-10000-workers-131957819.html">再裁员1万名</a>，以进一步削减成本。第一次裁员影响了其招聘团队，但该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-begins-its-latest-round-of-layoffs-145019127.html">在 4 月下旬</a>缩减了技术团队，并<a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-is-laying-off-employees-for-the-third-time-in-less-than-three-months-174112198.html">在 5 月下旬</a>缩减了业务部门。 Facebook 所有者希望通过减少管理层并要求一些领导者承担以前为普通员工保留的工作来简化其运营。 Meta 的员工人数可能需要一段时间才能再次增长——预计要到 2023 年底完成重组工作后才能解除招聘冻结。</p><h2>二月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/0d02d0e0-b856-11ed-bdff-3b6b0c6afd32" data-uuid="1f440042-5788-3939-9ef5-bbd6dc7740b1"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><h2>里维安裁员</h2><p>Rivian <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/rivian-ceo-memo-cost-cutting-layoffs-205556718.html">在 2022 年</a>进行了裁员，但这不足以帮助这个羽翼未丰的电动汽车品牌实现盈利。 2 月份，该公司又解雇了<a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/rivian-layoffs-184047174.html">6% 的员工</a>，即约 840 名员工。该公司仍在努力实现盈利，而供应链问题造成的产量短缺也无济于事。首席执行官 RJ Scaringe 表示，裁员将帮助 Rivian 专注于其业务“影响最大”的方面。</p><h2>变焦裁员</h2><p>Zoom 是<a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/zoom-earnings-214253721.html">疫情高峰期</a>远程工作文化的主要内容，因此，随着人们返回办公室，该公司削减开支也就不足为奇了。这家视频通话公司 2 月份表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/zoom-layoffs-202256575.html">裁员约 1,300 名员工</a>，占其员工总数的 15%。正如首席执行官埃里克·袁(Eric Yuan)所说，该公司在应对突如其来的成功时并没有“可持续地”招聘员工。据报道，裁员对于帮助度过困难的经济是必要的。管理团队提供的不仅仅是道歉。袁征将下一财年的工资削减 98%，而所有其他高管的基本工资以及 2023 财年奖金将减少 20%。</p><h2>雅虎裁员</h2><p>Engadget 的母公司雅虎也未能幸免于裁员。该互联网品牌在 2 月份表示，将在 2023 年<a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://www.axios.com/2023/02/09/yahoo-layoffs-2023-tech-media-companies">裁员超过 20%</a> ，即超过 1,600 人。其中大部分裁员（即大约 1,000 个职位）是立即进行的。不过，首席执行官吉姆·兰佐尼(Jim Lanzone)并未将裁员归咎于经济状况。相反，他将其定位为广告技术部门的重组，因为该部门放弃了一项不盈利的业务，​​转而支持一项成功的业务。实际上，雅虎正在退出与谷歌和 Meta 在广告市场的直接竞争。</p><h2>戴尔裁员</h2><p>大流行病的复苏和严峻的经济形势对个人电脑制造商的打击尤为严重，而戴尔所感受到的痛苦比大多数公司都要严重。在经历了残酷的第四季度（计算机出货量估计下降了 37%）之后，<a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dell-layoffs-144303513.html">该公司在 2 月初解雇了 5% 的</a>员工，即大约 6,650 名员工。戴尔表示，过去的成本削减努力还不够，据报道需要裁员和精简组织才能重回正轨。</p><h2> Deliveroo裁员</h2><p>送餐服务蓬勃发展，而新冠肺炎 (COVID-19) 疫情让人们远离餐馆，现在人们愿意再次外出就餐，至少有些人感受到了刺痛。 Deliveroo 将<a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Deliveroo UK;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3d6699dc-3184-47dd-a3f8-0e4b4c1dd37b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Deliveroo+UK&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeGBlzRDr0JyeLhwAuI8oqPUGfFz3VvJQ84vA3mdPgQ7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fdeliveroo.co.uk%2Fmore%2Fnews-articles%2Fwill-shu-message-to-deliveroo-employees">解雇约 350 名员工</a>，占其员工总数的 9%。创始人 Will Shu 表示，“重新部署”将使这个数字接近 300 人。理由很熟悉：舒表示，Deliveroo 迅速招聘员工来应对与疫情相关的“前所未有的”增长，但据报道，由于面临经济困难，该公司必须削减成本。</p><h2> DocuSign 裁员</h2><p>对于许多在线签署过文件的人来说，DocuSign 可能很熟悉，但这并没有使其免受恶劣经济环境的影响。该公司在 2 月中旬表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1261333/000126133323000007/docu-20230216.htm">裁员 10%</a> 。虽然没有透露具体人数，但截至 2022 年初，该公司拥有 7,461 名员工。大多数失业人员在 DocuSign 的全球现场组织工作。</p><h2>亚搏体育appGitLab裁员</h2><p>您可能不知道 GitLab，但它的 DevOps（开发和运营）平台支撑着 NVIDIA 和 T-Mobile 等科技品牌的工作，而其客户业务的萎缩正在影响其利润。 GitLab 将<a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://about.gitlab.com/blog/2023/02/09/gitlab-news/">解雇 7% 的员工</a>，即大约 114 人。公司首席执行官西德·西布兰迪 (Sid Sijbrandij) 表示，经济问题意味着客户对软件投资采取“更加保守的态度”，而公司之前重新调整支出的尝试不足以应对这些挑战。</p><h2> GoDaddy 裁员</h2><p>GoDaddy 在疫情爆发初期就进行了裁员，当时其面向零售的社交平台裁掉了 800 多名员工。然而，今年二月，它采取了更广泛的行动。该网络服务提供商解雇了所有部门<a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://aboutus.godaddy.net/newsroom/press-releases/press-release-details/2023/A-message-from-GoDaddy-CEO-Aman-Bhutani/default.aspx">8% 的员工</a>，即 500 多人。首席执行官阿曼·布塔尼 (Aman Bhutani) 声称，其他形式的成本削减不足以帮助公司应对“不确定”的经济形势，这反映了进一步整合 Main Street Hub 等收购的努力。</p><h2> Twilio 裁员</h2><p>Twilio 在 2022 年 9 月裁减了 800 多个工作岗位，但随着 2023 年开始，它进行了更大幅度的裁员。该云通信品牌在 2 月中旬<a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1" href="https://www.twilio.com/blog/restructuring-twilio">解雇了 17% 的员工</a>，即大约 1,500 人。与许多其他科技公司一样，Twillio 表示，过去的成本削减努力不足以承受严酷的环境。它还将裁员合理化，以精简组织。</p><h2>一月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/f50d6cc0-d84a-11ec-b3ed-100a619b2c97" alt="2022 年 5 月 16 日，在参观位于美国加利福尼亚州山景城的谷歌新湾景园区时，BV100 大楼的外景。照片摄于 2022 年 5 月 16 日。REUTERS/Peter DaSilva" data-uuid="018fa580-4a3a-3a88-9d3f-09be5f04dff4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">路透社/彼得·达席尔瓦</div></figure><h2>谷歌（Alphabet）裁员</h2><p>谷歌母公司 Alphabet 一段时间以来一直在削减成本，包括<a data-i13n="cpos:30;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-shutting-down-stadia-162704135.html">关闭 Stadia</a> ，但该公司在 1 月底更进一步，表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:31;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-parent-alphabet-is-laying-off-12000-employees-105523115.html">裁员 12,000 名员工</a>。首席执行官桑达尔·皮查伊 (Sundar Pichai) 毫不掩饰其理由：Alphabet 一直在为“不同的经济现实”招聘人才，并正在进行重组，以专注于这家互联网巨头最重要的业务。这一决定对该公司 120 区孵化器的打击<a data-i13n="cpos:32;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-lays-off-most-employees-area-120-in-house-incubator-154329887.html">尤为严重</a>，该部门的大多数员工都失业了。 Intrinsic（机器人）和 Verily（健康）等子品牌也在大规模裁员前几天裁掉了大量员工。 Waymo 已<a data-i13n="cpos:33;pos:1" href="https://www.reuters.com/article/alphabet-layoffs-waymo-idCAKBN2V33PW">进行</a>两轮裁员，裁员 209 人，占员工总数的 8%。</p><h2>亚马逊裁员</h2><p>亚马逊去年秋天就已经 <a data-i13n="cpos:34;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-layoffs-report-191003720.html">制定了裁员计划</a>，但在 1 月初扩大了裁员范围，表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:35;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-expanded-job-cuts-18000-102059372.html">裁减 18,000 个工作岗位</a>，其中大部分来自零售和招聘团队。 3 月份，该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:36;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-will-lay-off-another-9000-employees-in-the-coming-weeks-152653190.html">又裁员 9,000 人</a>，4 月份又表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:37;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-lays-off-more-than-100-employees-across-its-gaming-divisions-190634108.html">有 100 多名游戏员工</a>离职。毫不奇怪，首席执行官安迪·贾西（Andy Jassy）将其归咎于“经济的不确定性”和近年来的快速招聘。随着人们转向网上购物，亚马逊从这一流行病中<a data-i13n="cpos:38;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-q1-2021-210221698.html">受益匪浅</a>，但随着人们回归实体店，其<a data-i13n="cpos:39;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-q1-2022-earnings-growth-235926922.html">增长正在放缓</a>。</p><h2> Coinbase 裁员</h2><p>Coinbase 是受 2022 年加密货币市场低迷影响的较大公司之一，这种影响一直延续到新的一年。该加密货币交易所在 1 月中旬<a data-i13n="cpos:40;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/coinbase-lay-offs-reduced-expenses-153433234.html">裁员 950 人</a>，而就在几个月前，该<a data-i13n="cpos:41;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/coinbase-job-cuts-layoffs-150838290.html">交易所还裁员 1,100 人</a>。这是大型科技品牌中规模最大的裁员之一——Coinbase 裁掉了约五分之一的员工。首席执行官布莱恩·阿姆斯特朗表示，他的公司需要裁员来缩减运营开支，并度过他之前所说的“加密货币冬天”，但这也意味着取消一些不太可能成功的项目。</p><h2> IBM裁员</h2><p>裁员有时更多地源于公司战略转变，而不是财务困难，IBM 在 2023 年提供了一个典型的例子。这家计算先驱在秋季剥离了人工智能驱动的 Watson Health 业务和基础设施管理部门（现为 Kyndryl）后，于 1 月下旬<a data-i13n="cpos:42;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-01-25/ibm-to-cut-about-3-900-workers-still-hiring-in-higher-growth-areas?sref=10lNAhZ9">裁减了 3,900 个工作岗位</a>。简而言之，随着 IBM 转向云计算，这些员工没有什么可做的。</p><h2>微软裁员</h2><p>微软开始了公司历史上第二大裁员潮，该公司表示将在 1 月中旬至 3 月底期间<a data-i13n="cpos:43;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-confirms-layoffs-151816595.html">裁员 10,000 人</a>。与许多其他科技巨头一样，随着客户在大流行复苏期间<a data-i13n="cpos:44;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-q2-fy23-earnings-report-211718819.html">缩减支出</a>（特别是在 Windows 和设备上），该公司正在削减成本。这种裁员对一些部门来说尤其痛苦——据报道，他们<a data-i13n="cpos:45;pos:1" href="https://www.windowscentral.com/microsoft/microsoft-has-laid-off-entire-teams-behind-virtual-mixed-reality-and-hololens">摧毁了 HoloLens 和混合现实团队</a>，而 343 Industries 则在失去数十名员工后据信正在<a data-i13n="cpos:46;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/343-industries-halo-unreal-engine-202439779.html">重启 Halo 开发</a>。 GitHub 正在<a data-i13n="cpos:47;pos:1" href="https://siliconangle.com/2023/02/09/github-gitlab-announce-job-cuts/">裁员 10%</a> ，即大约 300 人。</p><h2>贝宝裁员</h2><p>PayPal 一直是健康状况较好的大型科技公司之一，去年第三季度的<a data-i13n="cpos:48;pos:1" href="https://s201.q4cdn.com/231198771/files/doc_financials/2022/q3/PYPL-Q3-22-Earnings-Release.pdf">业绩超出了预期</a>。尽管如此，它也未能幸免于经济不景气的影响。这家在线支付公司于 1 月底公布了<a data-i13n="cpos:49;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/paypal-is-laying-off-2000-employees-212108119.html">裁员 2,000 名员工</a>的计划，占其员工总数的 7%。首席执行官丹·舒尔曼 (Dan Schulman) 声称，裁员将控制成本，并帮助 PayPal 专注于“核心战略重点”。</p><h2> Salesforce 裁员</h2><p>Salesforce 为 2023 年定下了基调，在新年仅四天后，该公司就警告称将<a data-i13n="cpos:50;pos:1" href="https://www.sec.gov/ix?doc=/Archives/edgar/data/0001108524/000110852423000003/crm-20230104.htm">裁员 8,000 名员工</a>，约占员工总数的 10%。尽管该云软件品牌在疫情期间蓬勃发展，收入快速增长，但它承认在繁荣时期过于积极地招聘员工，在经济衰退时无法维持这一员工水平。</p><h2> SAP裁员</h2><p>商业软件巨头 SAP 的利润在 2022 年底大幅下降 68%，并从 2023 年开始<a data-i13n="cpos:51;pos:1" href="https://news.sap.com/2023/01/sap-announces-fourth-quarter-and-full-year-2022-results/">裁员 2,800 名员工</a>以保持业务健康发展。不过，与科技领域的一些知名企业不同的是，SAP 并没有将裁员归咎于大流行时期的过度招聘。相反，它将这一举措描述为一家仍预计 2023 年加速增长的公司的“有针对性的重组”。</p><h2> Spotify 裁员</h2><p>近年来，Spotify 大力投资<a data-i13n="cpos:52;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-05-spotify-podcasts-the-ringer.html">扩大其播客帝国</a>，但在 2023 年开始时很快就停止了这种做法。这家流媒体音乐服务公司在 1 月底表示，将<a data-i13n="cpos:53;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-will-lay-off-6-percent-of-employees-130337498.html">裁员 6%</a> （截至第三季度，Spotify 有 9,800 名员工），同时进行重组工作，其中包括内容主管 Dawn Ostroff 的离职。尽管 2022 年的高级订阅用户数量比以往任何时候都多，但该公司也<a data-i13n="cpos:54;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-reaches-205-million-premium-subscribers-as-losses-mount-122503157.html">遭受了巨大损失</a>——首席执行官丹尼尔·埃克 (Daniel Ek) 表示，在收入无法支撑之前，他的投资“过于雄心勃勃”。</p><h2> Wayfair裁员</h2><p>亚马逊并不是唯一一家在 2023 年缩减规模的大型在线零售商。Wayfair 在 1 月底表示，将<a data-i13n="cpos:55;pos:1" href="https://investor.wayfair.com/news/news-details/2023/Wayfair-Announces-Update-to-Cost-Efficiency-Plan-and-Business-Performance/default.aspx">裁员 1,750 名团队成员</a>，占其全球员工总数的 10%。其中约 1,200 名员工被裁减，目的是“消除管理层”，并以其他方式帮助公司变得更精简、更灵活。 Wayfair 自 2022 年 8 月以来一直在削减成本（包括 870 个职位），但认为裁员有助于其比预期更早实现盈亏平衡。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/big-tech-layoffs-2023-152856197.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/big-tech-layoffs-2023-152856197.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ebb49371-5396-4cbe-9ddd-56da42a4f377</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 18:25:22 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689877524</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T18:25:36+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Unemployment Issues]]></category><category><![CDATA[Budget, Tax & Economy]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="3716" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-01/94cbe9d0-9cc7-11ed-9daf-521efd1c29f0" width="5858"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3716" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-01/94cbe9d0-9cc7-11ed-9daf-521efd1c29f0" width="5858"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Westend61 via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Businessman carrying box with personal belongings on sunny day]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Dolphin’s Wii and GameCube emulator isn’t coming to Steam after all]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Dolphin Emulator 这个可以让你玩旧版 Wii 和 GameCube 游戏的软件最终不会<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dolphin-is-releasing-its-gamecube-and-wii-emulator-on-steam-193356400.html">出现在 Steam 上</a>。 The developers published a <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://dolphin-emu.org/blog/2023/07/20/what-happened-to-dolphin-on-steam/">blog post</a> today explaining how the <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dolphin-emulator-steam-release-delayed-indefinitely-following-nintendo-dmca-notice-194601894.html">fumbled launch</a> went down — and why they still believe they were in the right legally. In short, Nintendo&#39;s lawyers didn&#39;t want it on Steam, and Valve wasn&#39;t about to take a stand in a potential showdown with a fellow gaming behemoth.</p><p> The emulator&#39;s creators explained that, contrary to online perceptions, Nintendo didn&#39;t send the team a DMCA takedown notice (or any other legal action). However, Valve&#39;s legal department contacted Nintendo, asking about the planned release of the app that could run old games like <em>Super Mario Galaxy</em> , <em>Wii Sports</em> and <em>The Legend of Zelda: Majora&#39;s Mask</em> through the ubiquitous PC storefront. Valve then forwarded a statement from Nintendo&#39;s lawyers to the Dolphin team and told them they could only launch the emulator if Nintendo approved. “We specifically request that Dolphin&#39;s &#39;coming soon&#39; notice be removed and that you ensure the emulator does not release on the Steam store moving forward,” Nintendo&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://dolphin-emu.org/m/user/blog/steam-release/lettertovalve.png">letter to Valve</a> read. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/9a857fd0-2719-11ee-bed4-ba493caa78c9" style="height:750px;width:1200px;" alt="Screenshot of the (canceled) Dolphin Emulator for Steam. A large title says" data-uuid="62a62034-d02f-3236-bdf7-677b9fbc071b"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Dolphin</div></figure><p> It sounds like Valve didn&#39;t want to get involved and instead put the onus on Dolphin&#39;s developers to get permission which everyone involved must have known wouldn&#39;t have been granted. Considering how <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-s-lawsuit-forces-japanese-dev-to-cough-up-30-1847420631">quick a trigger</a> Nintendo&#39;s lawyers have had in the past — coupled with the wording of the letter they sent about the matter — the development team saw the writing on the wall and pulled the plug on the Steam release. Of course, the Dolphin Emulator is <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://dolphin-emu.org">still available</a> as a discrete download for Windows, macOS and Linux from the project&#39;s website. However, having it on Steam could have boosted its perceived legitimacy and opened it up to a much wider audience.</p><p> “Valve ultimately runs the store and can set any condition they wish for software to appear on it,” the Dolphin team wrote today. “But given Nintendo&#39;s long-held stance on emulation, we find Valve&#39;s requirement for us to get approval from Nintendo for a Steam release to be impossible. Unfortunately, that&#39;s that.”</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/dolphins-wii-and-gamecube-emulator-isnt-coming-to-steam-after-all-170029820.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/dolphins-wii-and-gamecube-emulator-isnt-coming-to-steam-after-all-170029820.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 3d05c37e-574f-4685-9970-84b7d5f7cebe</guid><dc:creator> Will Shanklin</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 17:00:29 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689871716</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T16:48:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="1059" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/6e62c0f0-271b-11ee-b34f-a0c2d24bda76" width="1500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1059" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/6e62c0f0-271b-11ee-b34f-a0c2d24bda76" width="1500"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Nintendo]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Game art of Mario riding Yoshi through space with a star character floating next to them. A small green planet, shaped like Mario’s head (with green grass for ‘hair’) looms behind them.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Super Mario Galaxy 2]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best wireless workout headphones for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> As some of you might know, I&#39;m a runner. On occasion I review sports watches, and outside of work I&#39;m a certified marathon coach. So when Engadget wanted to round up the best wireless earbuds for workouts, I raised my hand.</p><p> In addition to fit and battery life, I considered factors such as style; build quality; ease of use; the charging case; the strength of the Bluetooth connection; support for assistants such as Siri and Alexa; water resistance ratings; and audio features such as background noise cancelation and ambient sound modes. You&#39;ll notice I don&#39;t have much if anything to say about sound quality. Engadget&#39;s resident expert Billy Steele has written plenty about the listening experience in his standalone reviews, which I&#39;ve linked throughout, but for my purposes the differences were too subtle to make or break a purchasing decision.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> In the end, I never quite mastered some of the over-complicated controls, but at no point did an earbud fall out while I was exercising. I also never came close to running out of juice. So, participation trophies for everyone? Ha: The companies wish. I do indeed have some top picks, while I found some others fell short in key areas.</p><h2> How we tested</h2><h3> Water resistance</h3><p> Even if earbuds aren&#39;t marketed specifically as workout headphones, a sturdy, water-resistant design will, by default, make them suitable for exercise. To avoid repeating myself throughout this guide, I&#39;ll drop a quick primer here on durability, or ingression protection (IP), ratings. The first digit you&#39;ll see after the “IP” refers to protection from dust and other potential intrusions. That spec is measured on a scale of 1 to 6. The second refers to water resistance or even waterproofing, in the best cases. Higher numbers mean more protection, while the letter “X” means the device is not rated for protection in that regard. The ratings for water resistance are ranked on a scale of 1 to 9.</p><p> All but one of the best workout headphones we tested for this guide is rated IPX4. That means there&#39;s no dust protection, and the buds can withstand splashes from any direction, and are sweat resistant, but probably shouldn&#39;t be submerged. The most durable set of true wireless earbuds we tested, Jabra&#39;s Elite Active 4, is rated IP57, which means a high level of both dust and water protection. Whereas the IPX 4 models can handle splashes, the Elite Active 4 can be immersed for up to 30 minutes in up to a meter (or about 3.2 feet) of water.</p><p> For a detailed breakdown of all the possible permutations, I recommend checking out <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.enclosurecompany.com/ip-ratings-explained.php">this guide</a> published by a supplier called The Enclosure Company.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> <strong>Earbuds we tested</strong></p></td><td><p> <strong>Durability rating</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> Beats Powerbeats Pro</p></td><td><p> IPX4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> Beats Fit Pro</p></td><td><p> IPX4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> Jabra Elite Active 4</p></td><td><p> IP57</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> Sony WF-C500</p></td><td><p> IPX4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> Anker Soundcore Liberty 3 Pro</p></td><td><p> IPX4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h3><br> Active noise cancelation</h3><p> For the 2022 update to this guide, I decided to add a note up top about active noise cancelation (ANC), simply because most of the available models now offer it. And since the user experience is actually pretty similar across different brands, I thought it would be easier to share what noise canceling features they have in common, rather than repeat myself.</p><p> First of all, no noise cancellation is perfect. If you&#39;re looking for sport earbuds that you can continue wearing even after you&#39;re done working out, you might still hear some noise from the outside world, whether it be your robot vacuum or cars honking. The difference in quality with ANC enabled is undeniable; just don&#39;t take these companies&#39; marketing claims too literally. Besides, I don&#39;t recommend active noise cancellation while exercising outdoors; it&#39;s not safe. And even if you are working out indoors, I still think a noise cancellation horse race is probably beside the point for the purpose of this guide.</p><h2> The best wireless workout headphones all around: Jabra Elite 4 Active </h2><p><core-commerce id="7dd27b57f32a48a09a99ca50fff30e02" data-type="product-list"></p><ul><li><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Reasonably priced for the feature set; sleek, compact design; one of the lightest charging cases we tested (and some of the longest battery life); more durable than most; active noise cancelation, a transparency mode and customizable equalizer; works with Spotify Tap on Android.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Onboard controls aren&#39;t intuitive, but Jabra offers helpful instructions in its app; less comfortable after prolonged use than other brands.</p></li></ul><p><br> Much like the Elite Active 75t we tested a few years back, the newer <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARnYSsBT4JpYdlSIBF9YSIbrkNj84GEq3S8C-kbzaxfn&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FJabra-Active-Bluetooth-Earbuds-Built%2Fdp%2FB09MVGQRDD%3Fth%3D1">Elite Active 4 earbuds</a> make a strong first impression, with a compact, stylish design and a lightweight charging case to match. Available in three colors, the earbuds aren&#39;t just small and light, but they look especially sleek given that they don&#39;t have any wingtips. Though they felt comfortable when I first put them in, my ears did feel a little sore by the end of a run.</p><p> Meanwhile, the 37.5-gram case is also among the lightest we tested, but still offers some of the longest battery life, promising a total of 28 hours. (Each individual earbud on its own is rated for seven hours. Jabra says you can return to an hour&#39;s worth of juice after a 10-minute charge.)</p><p> In my testing, the earbuds were easy to insert and pair. Less easy is learning how to use the things. As you might expect, you press the right earbud once to stop and resume playback. You can also double-press the right bud to skip a track, and triple press it to play it again. But some of the other onboard controls are less obvious. To increase the volume, hold down the right earbud for a second; to lower it, long press the left earbud. Meanwhile, single-pressing the left earbud allows you to toggle between active noise cancelation, HearThrough mode, or neither. Lastly, double press the left bud to use a voice assistant.</p><p> The good news is, you don&#39;t have to commit all those finger gestures to memory: Jabra&#39;s Sound+ App for iOS and Android contains a helpful illustrated tutorial, which I recommend keeping open on your phone as you get settled in with your new earbuds.</p><p> I mastered the controls quickly enough, but the physical buttons on the earbuds require a little more pressure and coordination to get an accurate press in. I found myself waiting until I had slowed to a walk before I started fiddling with the tracks. Even then, I needed to be very deliberate to make sure I got it right. And usually I did. That said, given there&#39;s no physical volume rocker, I did wish there were an aural cue confirming I had moved the volume up or down a notch; the progression from louder to softer (or vice versa) is very subtle.</p><p> After a roughly 35-minute run the battery was still at 90 percent – a similar showing to what I saw on the Beats Fit Pro, also featured in this guide. Like the Elite Active 75t I tested previously, the Elite 4 Active uses Jabra&#39;s HearThrough technology. With that enabled, I could hear cars along my running route, though on an especially windy day the gusts drowned out softer noises like footsteps behind me. That&#39;s despite the earbuds having four built-in mics with what Jabra calls a “mesh covering” for added wind noise reduction.</p><p> Although I tested the Elite 4 Active on an iPhone 12, the earbuds have some additional features on Android, including support for Spotify Tap, which resumes where you last left off listening to your Spotify account on any device. Android users also get support for Alexa and Google&#39;s Fast Pair tech.</p><p> While I recommend the Elite 4 Active for most people, it&#39;s also worth quickly mentioning the <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUy7hmzcCdH3_xCP_qbebYgcWxE18Ot9b99fmkgi3sbK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FJabra-Elite-Active-Bluetooth-Earbuds%2Fdp%2FB09D15G8PG%3Fth%3D1">Elite 7 Active</a> , which adds Jabra&#39;s ShakeGrip technology for what the company claims is a more secure fit. You also get slightly better battery life – eight hours per bud, or 30 hours with the case – and even faster charging (an hour of playback after a five-minute charge). Lastly, choosing the Elite 7 Active over the Elite 4 Active gives you the option of either Google Assistant or Alexa, as well as voice guidance. However, you&#39;d be giving up call controls, which you do get on the Elite 4 Active.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/jabra-elite-4-active-review-140024466.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of Jabra Elite 4 Active</strong></a></p><h2> The most comfortable wireless workout headphones: Beats Powerbeats Pro </h2><p><core-commerce id="76984aa759f44c3ab8c33f689873676d" data-type="product-list"></p><ul><li><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Comfortable, stable fit; pairs seamlessly with iOS devices; intuitive controls with mirrored access on the left and right sides; tied with Sony for the longest earbud battery life.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Ear-hook design isn&#39;t the most discreet, and doesn&#39;t fit so well with sunglasses; relatively heavy charging case; no active noise cancelation, transparency mode or customizable EQ; speaking to an assistant is slightly less convenient if it&#39;s not Siri.</p></li></ul><p><br> For the purposes of this guide I tested two pairs of Beats headphones: the <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlKTDQxTjlDL3JlZj1mc19hX2J0Ml91czE_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8ta2MtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjU1NmJlMmUwLWRiOTYtMzI2ZC1iNTg3LWNhOWNlYTAwOTRjYiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAWFPdrEVVlXpzoWrYaCGgeRadqGmj1sPVmFxo7zyZRsP&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09JL41N9C%2Fref%3Dfs_a_bt2_us1">Beats Fit Pro</a> earbuds, and the <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZPv0blVE_Qjfb-Ush6-ic8L71InYASz89F-9Nw1mSWT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPowerbeats-Pro-Totally-Wireless-Earphones%2Fdp%2FB07R5QD598%3F">Powerbeats Pro</a> , earbuds with an over-the-ear hook design. I&#39;ll start with the Powerbeats Pro, which I like better for exercising.</p><p> Other than being slightly conspicuous, the Powerbeats Pro comes in four colors and fits comfortably, though it doesn&#39;t play as nicely with glasses and face masks as more compact in-ear designs. Compared to the other earbuds I tested, though, I felt especially confident the Powerbeats Pro would stay put during workouts.</p><p> Like Apple&#39;s newest AirPods, the Powerbeats Pro use Apple&#39;s H1 chip, which allows for particularly deep integration when you pair the earbuds with an Apple-made device. In addition to a fast, seamless pairing process, you can activate Siri by saying “Hey Siri,” without having to press a button. You can also share audio with other AirPods or Beats headphones, and can enjoy automatic switching between Apple devices.</p><p> For better and worse, the integration is so complete, in fact, that there&#39;s no companion app; instead you check the earbuds&#39; and cases&#39; battery via other methods, such as a homescreen widget or by asking Siri.</p><p> The earbuds themselves are rated for nine hours of use, which is among the highest we&#39;ve seen. The case is rated for a total of 24 hours of use, which isn&#39;t bad, but given that it&#39;s not best in class you have to wonder why the case is as heavy as it is. (Heavy enough that my purse feels a little lighter without it.) iOS users won&#39;t mind that the case charges via a Lightning cable and not USB-C, but others might be slightly put out.</p><p> If you&#39;ve ever used AirPods or Apple&#39;s old-school wired headphones, these should be pretty easy to master. Double-press the physical button on the earbud to skip tracks and triple-press it to go backward. I quickly came to love the physical key; it&#39;s less finicky than a touch surface. I was also grateful for the mirroring of controls between the left and right earbuds — both left- and right-handed people should be happy.</p><p> Having tested other wireless earbuds that either lack onboard volume controls, or make it tedious, I have come to particularly appreciate the Powerbeats Pro&#39;s onboard volume rockers – one for each earbud. I don&#39;t know of any other workout earbuds that make it easier to adjust the volume, not even the Beats Fit Pro.</p><p> While it&#39;s nice to have easier volume access, the audio experience is otherwise basic. There is no active noise cancellation or transparency mode. Not a dealbreaker for workouts, but something to consider if you&#39;re an audiophile or your goal is to get one pair of earbuds you can wear for everything.</p><p> Other features include support for voice assistants (yes, Google and Amazon too), but only Siri can be summoned by a voice command. You can also wear just one bud if you like (the right one) if all you need to do is talk on the phone, or if you want to keep an ear open to what&#39;s going on around you.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-05-16-beats-powerbeats-pro-review.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of Beats Powerbeats Pro</strong></a></p><h2> Honorable mention: Beats Fit Pro </h2><p><core-commerce id="4079bd5ed9384747a896daddef8e2e32" data-type="product-list"></p><ul><li><p> <strong>Pros</strong> : Comfortable, stable fit; pairs easily with iOS devices; compact, lightweight charging case; adds ANC and transparency modes, which the Powerbeats Pro lacks.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> A smaller design than the Powerbeats Pro means shorter battery life and the loss of a physical volume rocker; no customizable EQ.</p></li></ul><p><br> One of my main complaints about the Powerbeats Pro is that they don&#39;t fit as well if you&#39;re wearing sunglasses (or, in pandemic times a mask). This is where the <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlKTDQxTjlDL3JlZj1mc19hX2J0Ml91czE_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8ta2MtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjU1NmJlMmUwLWRiOTYtMzI2ZC1iNTg3LWNhOWNlYTAwOTRjYiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAWFPdrEVVlXpzoWrYaCGgeRadqGmj1sPVmFxo7zyZRsP&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09JL41N9C%2Fref%3Dfs_a_bt2_us1">Beats Fit Pro</a> have the advantage: Their discreet design that promises to stay out of the way and safe even during sweaty workouts.</p><p> Available in four colors, the buds are easy to insert and comfortable to wear – just twist the bud to fold the wingtip into your upper ear. And, because the earbuds are smaller than the Powerbeats Pro, the case is markedly lighter and more compact (55g versus 80g on the Pro). Between the lightweight case and the less dorky design, the Beats Fit Pro make a strong case for themselves as earbuds you can wear not just during workouts, but everywhere.</p><p> Because the Beats Fit Pro were released more recently than the Powerbeats Pro, they have active noise cancellation, a feature older Powerbeats and AirPods products are lacking. At the same time, Apple built in a transparency mode – ideal for runners like me who would feel safer if they could still hear ambient cues like footsteps and car horns. Lastly, it supports Apple&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/spatial%20audio/">Spatial Audio</a> format for a more immersive sound and will automatically kick in if you&#39;re playing a compatible track.</p><p> For working out, the audio is fine. But if you can only afford one pair of earbuds, my colleague Billy Steele indicated in his <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/beats-fit-pro-review-140004462.html">review</a> that the sound quality is mediocre. He found calls could be patchy and, as he notes, Beats is one of the few brands that doesn&#39;t offer users a customizable EQ.</p><p> Out of the box, the earbuds are set to active noise cancellation. There are two ways to adjust this: You can hold down the physical button on either earbud to cycle through audio profiles. Or, you can find the earbuds in your Bluetooth settings menu and click further to see a more detailed menu of options. Not only can you adjust the mode there, but you can also change what those physical buttons do. By default, they&#39;re for toggling audio profiles, but you can also set them up so that one earbud controls volume up, and the other volume down. Personally, I preferred having the option of adjusting the volume from my earbuds mid-workout; it&#39;s easy to just pick an audio mode before your run and stick with it.</p><p> Other than the slightly limited volume controls, the Beats Fit Pro works much like other Beats- and Apple-branded headphones. Press the physical button once to play or pause tracks; double press to skip forward; and triple press to replay a track. For anyone upgrading from an older pair of Beats or Apple earbuds, the transition should be easy. My only word of caution is that I found the physical button on the Beats Fit Pro harder to find by feel, as it&#39;s smaller and less indented than the button on the Powerbeats Pro.</p><p> Apple rates the Beats Fit Pro for six hours of listening time per earbud, plus an additional 18 hours from the USB-C charging case. You can also wear just one bud if you like, to squeeze out even more runtime. In my testing, the battery on the buds dropped down to 89 percent after a 35-minute run. Extrapolate that, and the math comes close to Apple&#39;s six-hours-per-bud claim. If you&#39;ve managed to completely exhaust both the earbud and case, Apple says its “Fast Fuel” feature will get you back to one hour of use after five minutes of charging, the same claim Jabra makes for the comparably priced Elite Active 7. (Note: Apple&#39;s one-hour estimate assumes you won&#39;t be using ANC.)</p><p> Under the hood, the earbuds have the same Apple-made H1 chip as the Powerbeats Pro and Apple&#39;s newer AirPods, allowing for hands-free “Hey Siri,” audio sharing with other AirPods or Beats headphones, and automatic switching between devices. The headphones also work with the Find My app, even on Android devices.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/beats-fit-pro-review-140004462.html"><strong>Read our Full Review of Beats Fit Pro</strong></a></p><h2> The best budget workout earbuds: Sony WF-C500 </h2><p><core-commerce id="9b84f746c6ee43e9919d94d6c4c90ee8" data-type="product-list"></p><ul><li><p> <strong>What you get:</strong> Reasonably priced earbuds that prioritize a light design and good audio quality.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Lightweight; reasonably priced; support for Sony&#39;s 360 Reality Audio format; the earbuds themselves claim relatively long battery life; customizable EQ; supports Google Fast Pair.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> No ANC or transparency mode; slightly trickier to pair on iOS than other earbuds we tested; the charging case has lower capacity than competing models; they have a larger, more bulbous design than others we tested (but are no less comfortable).</p></li></ul><p><br> With the <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXjxziBl6ndakQxiVD6fKSBxSdl5kFLGJ7A8pZQ1loYj&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-Wireless-Bluetooth-Headphones-resistance%2Fdp%2FB09CFP6J6D%3F">WF-C500 earbuds</a> , Sony is really emphasizing the small design: The earbuds themselves weigh 5.46 grams, while the charging case is 35g. That would be the lightest case we tested, and nearly the lightest pair of earbuds, barring the much pricier Elite Active 7. It&#39;s worth noting that a lighter charging case means shorter case battery life (a relatively low 20 hours). Even then, the earbuds themselves offer some of the longest battery life of the bunch: 10 hours per bud. If you do run low on charge, you can get back up to an hour&#39;s worth of capacity in 10 minutes, Sony says.</p><p> The earbuds, available in four colors, were larger than I was expecting given their light weight, but they&#39;re easy to insert and fit comfortably. They are slightly trickier for iPhone users to pair on iOS than other buds I tested for this guide, though Android users will benefit from support for Google Fast Pair.</p><p> By default, a robotic voice will tell you the earbuds&#39; battery charge as you&#39;re putting them in. I found this useful, though it meant that there was a delay in getting to hear whatever I had been listening to. You can always disable voice guidance in Sony&#39;s Headphones app if that bothers you.</p><p> The truth is, I rarely had range anxiety with these headphones anyway: Unlike other earbuds, which took a roughly 10 percent hit after my usual 35-minute run, these were still at 100 percent. It&#39;s unlikely I&#39;ll ever wear out both the buds and charging case before getting to a wall charger.</p><p> The controls were also easy to master without having to consult Sony&#39;s companion app. On the right earbud, press once to play or pause audio playback, or to answer or end a call. Double press to skip tracks, and triple press to go to the previous song. Long-pressing the right earbud launches or cancels a voice assistant. You can also long press to decline a call. On the left earbud, some of the controls are mirrored: you can press once to receive/end a call, and long-press to reject it. The left bud is also where the volume controls live: press once to raise it, and hold the button down to lower it.</p><p> As one of the options in this guide with a lower price tag, the WF-C500 are the only ones without active noise cancellation. Which to me, isn&#39;t a dealbreaker. The eartips already do a good enough job passively blocking noise, to the point where I was startled when a group of runners ran up from behind in the park and passed me. If anything, I wished the earbuds had a transparency mode that would allow more ambient noise through. Fortunately I could still hear louder noises like nearby traffic.</p><p> The lack of ANC aside, the audio quality is quite good – which makes sense, given Sony&#39;s heritage in audio and home theater gear. Like other models listed here (barring Beats, anyway), you can adjust the EQ in the companion app. And, as you might expect, the earbuds support Sony&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/360%20reality%20audio/">360 Reality Audio</a> format, which is similar to Apple&#39;s spatial tech, which in turn i <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-music-lossless-dolby-atmos-131659010.html">s built on the Dolby Atmos format</a> .</p><h2> The most customizable wireless workout headphones: Anker Soundcore Liberty 3 Pro </h2><p><core-commerce id="319c38d297da460ea0f668c56b6fdf75" data-type="product-list"></p><ul><li><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> The only buds we tested with wireless charging; long battery life, especially on the charging case; active noise cancelation, a transparency mode and customizable equalizer; lots of options for setting up the controls to your liking.</p></li><li><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Larger and a little harder to insert than competing models; touch-sensitive controls can be finicky; worse sound quality than the competition; in-app battery indicator doesn&#39;t give you a percentage.</p></li></ul><p><br> The <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Tb3VuZGNvcmUtTGliZXJ0eS1DYW5jZWxsaW5nLVdpcmVsZXNzLVBsYXl0aW1lL2RwL0IwOUNHTTFCV0g_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1rYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTU2YmUyZTAtZGI5Ni0zMjZkLWI1ODctY2E5Y2VhMDA5NGNiIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAde2BoD6n_AfSmNUAp0R-Ra2dHS1ljHNI9QZ4juWmqdG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSoundcore-Liberty-Cancelling-Wireless-Playtime%2Fdp%2FB09CGM1BWH%3Fth%3D1">Soundcore Liberty 3 Pro</a> earbuds are available in four colors, and carry a big emphasis on ergonomic fit. That includes air-filled wings, silicone ear tips (similar to other brands) and a promise of air-pressure relief, per Anker. The earbuds don&#39;t come with the eartips or wingtips attached, which adds some friction to the setup process but, on the plus side, you get a choice of four ear tip sizes, compared with three from most other headphone makers. Inside the Soundcore app you&#39;ll find a fit test, but I actually ended up with a more comfortable fit by just following my gut. But it&#39;s certainly worth playing around with.</p><p> The Liberty 3 Pro is right up there with the Sony CF-500 in terms of being some of the larger earbuds I tested for this guide. That said, they fit comfortably and stay put. I will say, however, that these were consistently harder to insert than some other brands I tested, even after I&#39;d had a bit of practice.</p><p> When I originally published this guide, in September 2020, I ruled out Anker&#39;s $55 Soundcore Spirit Dot 2 wireless earbuds on account of their fussy touch controls and the fact that you couldn&#39;t adjust the volume from the buds themselves. I&#39;m happy to report that the situation has improved – mostly. First, the bad news: The controls are still finicky, and especially difficult to get right while moving. But, they do offer volume control. (Thank goodness.) The controls are also programmable inside the Soundcore app. So you can at least customize the long press and single, double and triple taps in a way that feels intuitive. In addition to music and volume playback, you can also use the controls to toggle audio modes or to activate a voice assistant (Google or Alexa).</p><p> Just as you can modify the earbud controls, you have options as far as sound quality, too. There are ANC and transparency modes, along with a “normal” setting in between. Also, like Sony and Jabra, Anker allows for customization of the EQ from within the app. Interestingly, wind reduction is a feature you have to actively opt into. Anker says this is because the wind reducing mode dings ANC performance, and since it&#39;s unlikely people will often find themselves in strong winds, it may as well not be turned on by default. Later this year, Anker will push out a software update that will add “enhanced vocal mode,” which promises to increase vocal pickup in the area around you, according to an Anker spokesperson.</p><p> Additionally, Anker touts three mics per earbud, along with AI noise reduction. I can&#39;t prove that there&#39;s a connection here, but I did notice they sounded a little tinnier compared with other headphones. Sometimes, some random buzz even crept in. It&#39;s hard to know if that slight distortion is a result of the AI doing its work, but I wonder.</p><p> The Soundcore Liberty 3 Pro has the distinction of being the only earbuds we tested for this guide with a case that can charge wirelessly. The buds themselves are rated for eight hours of battery life apiece, or 32 hours with the case, making this the longest-lasting charging case we tested for this story. Anker also says that you can return to three hours of capacity after 15 minutes of charging. After a 35-minute run, the battery indicator in the app showed a mostly full charge, though unfortunately Anker doesn&#39;t give you a percentage.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-wireless-workout-headphones-191517835.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-wireless-workout-headphones-191517835.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 556be2e0-db96-326d-b587-ca9cea0094cb</guid><dc:creator> Dana Wollman</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 16:45:48 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689871548</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T16:46:13+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Sony]]></category><category><![CDATA[WF-SP800N]]></category><category><![CDATA[JLab]]></category><category><![CDATA[headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[earbuds]]></category><category><![CDATA[thebuyersguide]]></category><category><![CDATA[wirelessheadphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[BeatsPowerbeatsPro]]></category><category><![CDATA[commerce]]></category><category><![CDATA[Beats]]></category><category><![CDATA[Anker]]></category><category><![CDATA[soundcore]]></category><category><![CDATA[PowerbeatsPro]]></category><category><![CDATA[Jabra]]></category><category><![CDATA[SonyWF-SP800N]]></category><category><![CDATA[spiritdot2]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[re